<Link id="l00133" /><CodeLine lineNumber="133"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &#96;available&#95;externally&#96; functions even if their desc are available. This</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="134"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// is because the desc is computed based on the original internal function</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="135"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// and it&#39;s substituted by the &#96;available&#95;externally&#96; function during link</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="136"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// time. However, when unstable IR or ODR violation issue occurs, the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="137"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// definitions of the same function across different translation units could</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="138"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// be different and result in different checksums. So we should use the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="139"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// state from the new (available&#95;externally) function, which is saved in its</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00140" /><CodeLine lineNumber="140"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// attribute.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00141" /><CodeLine lineNumber="141"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// TODO: If the function&#39;s profile only exists as nested inlinee profile in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00142" /><CodeLine lineNumber="142"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// a different module, we don&#39;t have the attr mismatch state(unknown), we</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00143" /><CodeLine lineNumber="143"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// need to fix it later.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00144" /><CodeLine lineNumber="144"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (IsAvailableExternallyLinkage || !<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a4de98a9acffcef5bb4b31862cb8c72ac">Desc</a>)</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00776" /><CodeLine lineNumber="776"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   to match. Additionally, if BB had not been visited before,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00777" /><CodeLine lineNumber="777"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   we mark it visited.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00778" /><CodeLine lineNumber="778"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00779" /><CodeLine lineNumber="779"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Only one edge is unknown and BB has already been visited.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00780" /><CodeLine lineNumber="780"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   In this case, we can compute the weight of the edge by</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00781" /><CodeLine lineNumber="781"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   subtracting the total block weight from all the known</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00782" /><CodeLine lineNumber="782"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   edge weights. If the edges weight more than BB, then the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00783" /><CodeLine lineNumber="783"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   edge of the last remaining edge is set to zero.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00784" /><CodeLine lineNumber="784"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00785" /><CodeLine lineNumber="785"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - There exists a self-referential edge and the weight of BB is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00786" /><CodeLine lineNumber="786"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   known. In this case, this edge can be based on BB&#39;s weight.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00787" /><CodeLine lineNumber="787"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   We add up all the other known edges and set the weight on</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00788" /><CodeLine lineNumber="788"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   the self-referential edge as we did in the previous case.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00789" /><CodeLine lineNumber="789"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00790" /><CodeLine lineNumber="790"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// In any other case, we must continue iterating. Eventually,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00791" /><CodeLine lineNumber="791"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// all edges will get a weight, or iteration will stop when</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00792" /><CodeLine lineNumber="792"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// it reaches SampleProfileMaxPropagateIterations.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00793" /><CodeLine lineNumber="793"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (NumUnknownEdges &lt;= 1) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00795" /><CodeLine lineNumber="795"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (NumUnknownEdges == 0) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00796" /><CodeLine lineNumber="796"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprofileloaderbaseimpl/#a425760bcf9be77e6a664a5997283a2e1">VisitedBlocks</a>.count(EC)) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00797" /><CodeLine lineNumber="797"><span class="doxyHighlight">            </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If we already know the weight of all edges, the weight of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00798" /><CodeLine lineNumber="798"><span class="doxyHighlight">            </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// basic block can be computed. It should be no larger than the sum</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00799" /><CodeLine lineNumber="799"><span class="doxyHighlight">            </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// of all edge weights.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00800" /><CodeLine lineNumber="800"><span class="doxyHighlight">            </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (TotalWeight &gt; BBWeight) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00801" /><CodeLine lineNumber="801"><span class="doxyHighlight">              BBWeight = TotalWeight;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00873" /><CodeLine lineNumber="873"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Build in/out edge lists for each basic block in the CFG.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00874" /><CodeLine lineNumber="874"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00875" /><CodeLine lineNumber="875"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// We are interested in unique edges. If a block B1 has multiple</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00900" /><CodeLine lineNumber="900"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Propagate weights into edges</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00901" /><CodeLine lineNumber="901"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00902" /><CodeLine lineNumber="902"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The following rules are applied to every block BB in the CFG:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00903" /><CodeLine lineNumber="903"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00904" /><CodeLine lineNumber="904"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// - If BB has a single predecessor/successor, then the weight</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00905" /><CodeLine lineNumber="905"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   of that edge is the weight of the block.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00906" /><CodeLine lineNumber="906"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00907" /><CodeLine lineNumber="907"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// - If all incoming or outgoing edges are known except one, and the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00908" /><CodeLine lineNumber="908"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   weight of the block is already known, the weight of the unknown</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00909" /><CodeLine lineNumber="909"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   edge will be the weight of the block minus the sum of all the known</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00910" /><CodeLine lineNumber="910"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   edges. If the sum of all the known edges is larger than BB&#39;s weight,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00911" /><CodeLine lineNumber="911"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   we set the unknown edge weight to zero.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00912" /><CodeLine lineNumber="912"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00913" /><CodeLine lineNumber="913"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// - If there is a self-referential edge, and the weight of the block is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00914" /><CodeLine lineNumber="914"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   known, the weight for that edge is set to the weight of the block</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00915" /><CodeLine lineNumber="915"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   minus the weight of the other incoming edges to that block (if</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00916" /><CodeLine lineNumber="916"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   known).</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00980" /><CodeLine lineNumber="980"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Generate branch weight metadata for all branches in \\p F.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00981" /><CodeLine lineNumber="981"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00982" /><CodeLine lineNumber="982"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Branch weights are computed out of instruction samples using a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00983" /><CodeLine lineNumber="983"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// propagation heuristic. Propagation proceeds in 3 phases:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00984" /><CodeLine lineNumber="984"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00985" /><CodeLine lineNumber="985"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// 1- Assignment of block weights. All the basic blocks in the function</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00986" /><CodeLine lineNumber="986"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    are initial assigned the same weight as their most frequently</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00987" /><CodeLine lineNumber="987"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    executed instruction.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00988" /><CodeLine lineNumber="988"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00989" /><CodeLine lineNumber="989"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// 2- Creation of equivalence classes. Since samples may be missing from</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00990" /><CodeLine lineNumber="990"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    blocks, we can fill in the gaps by setting the weights of all the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00991" /><CodeLine lineNumber="991"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    blocks in the same equivalence class to the same weight. To compute</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00992" /><CodeLine lineNumber="992"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    the concept of equivalence, we use dominance and loop information.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00993" /><CodeLine lineNumber="993"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    Two blocks B1 and B2 are in the same equivalence class if B1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00994" /><CodeLine lineNumber="994"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    dominates B2, B2 post-dominates B1 and both are in the same loop.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00995" /><CodeLine lineNumber="995"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00996" /><CodeLine lineNumber="996"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// 3- Propagation of block weights into edges. This uses a simple</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00997" /><CodeLine lineNumber="997"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    propagation heuristic. The following rules are applied to every</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00998" /><CodeLine lineNumber="998"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    block BB in the CFG:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00999" /><CodeLine lineNumber="999"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01000" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1000"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    - If BB has a single predecessor/successor, then the weight</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01001" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1001"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///      of that edge is the weight of the block.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01002" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1002"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01003" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1003"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    - If all the edges are known except one, and the weight of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01004" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1004"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///      block is already known, the weight of the unknown edge will</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01005" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1005"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///      be the weight of the block minus the sum of all the known</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01006" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1006"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///      edges. If the sum of all the known edges is larger than BB&#39;s weight,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01007" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1007"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///      we set the unknown edge weight to zero.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01008" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1008"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01009" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1009"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    - If there is a self-referential edge, and the weight of the block is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1010"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///      known, the weight for that edge is set to the weight of the block</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1011"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///      minus the weight of the other incoming edges to that block (if</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1012"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///      known).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1013"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1014"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Since this propagation is not guaranteed to finalize for every CFG, we</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1015"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// only allow it to proceed for a limited number of iterations (controlled</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01016" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1016"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// by -sample-profile-max-propagate-iterations).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01017" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1017"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01018" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1018"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// FIXME: Try to replace this propagation heuristic with a scheme</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01019" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1019"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// that is guaranteed to finalize. A work-list approach similar to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01020" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1020"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the standard value propagation algorithm used by SSA-CCP might</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01021" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1021"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// work here.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01022" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1022"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01023" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1023"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\param F The function to query.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01024" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1024"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01025" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1025"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\returns true if \\p F was modified. Returns false, otherwise.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01026" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1026"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">template</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">typename</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> BT&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01027" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1027" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprofileloaderbaseimpl/#a040b98a945772423eab83d2ce02f984a"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprofileloaderbaseimpl/#a040b98a945772423eab83d2ce02f984a">SampleProfileLoaderBaseImpl&lt;BT&gt;::computeAndPropagateWeights</a>(</span></CodeLine>
